{"TopicId":211914,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"Rewind instead of QuickSave - QuickLoad","CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-06T15:35:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-06T15:35:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving recorded events on the timeline allows players to rewind instead of using F5-F9.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course this works best when on-rails. Doing it during a physics simulation means having reversible physics.. which is harder to do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it\u0027s doable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-06T15:37:06Z\u0022 title=\u002202/06/2023 03:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 6, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Vl3d\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jastrone","CreatedById":208489,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-06T15:43:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnot very usefull and you would either have to save every position or reverse physics\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-06T15:46:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224228576\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211914\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675698224\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208489\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jastrone\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, jastrone said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnot very usefull and you would either have to save every position or reverse physics\n\u0